being\", \"from\": 1895, \"to\": 1905}, {\"ngram\": \"the image\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 1928}, {\"ngram\": \"interests\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1942}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 1952}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They include policies that regulate doping and genetic enhancement, set age limits and weight classes and, in the case of Parasports,establish classes for competition.\", \"from\": 1954, \"to\": 2121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2076, \"end\": 2086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parasports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Parasports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parasports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parasports\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"policies\", \"from\": 1967, \"to\": 1975}, {\"ngram\": \"doping\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 1996}, {\"ngram\": \"genetic enhancement\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2020}, {\"ngram\": \"age limits\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2036}, {\"ngram\": \"weight classes\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2055}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 2064, \"to\": 2072}, {\"ngram\": \"classes\", \"from\": 2097, \"to\": 2104}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2120}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Protective policies can also regulate whether athletes compete in men's or women's events.\", \"from\": 2123, \"to\": 2213, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Protective policies\", \"from\": 2123, \"to\": 2142}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2177}, {\"ngram\": \"men's or women's events\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2212}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But history shows that there are no conclusive ways to determine sex - and no consensus over the extent to which the distinction matters.\", \"from\": 2214, \"to\": 2351, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2225}, {\"ngram\": \"no conclusive ways\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2265}, {\"ngram\": \"sex\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2282}, {\"ngram\": \"the extent\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2317}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 1940s, sports' governing bodies began requiring womento submit letters from physiciansconfirming they were, in fact, women.\", \"from\": 2353, \"to\": 2483, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 1940s\", \"from\": 2356, \"to\": 2365}, {\"ngram\": \"sports' governing bodies\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2391}, {\"ngram\": \"womento submit letters\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2430}, {\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 2471, \"to\": 2475}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 1960s, some athletic organizationsbriefly required gynecological examsand visual inspections of unclothed women before turning, in 1967,to sex chromatin teststhat looked specifically for female-typical XX sex chromosomes.\", \"from\": 2485, \"to\": 2713, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2694, \"end\": 2696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.777575800394946e-22, \"text\": \"XX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 1960s\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2497}, {\"ngram\": \"unclothed women\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2603}, {\"ngram\": \"1967,to sex chromatin\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2644}, {\"ngram\": \"teststhat\", \"from\": 2645, \"to\": 2654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When, in the 1980s, it finally became clear that women could have the male-typical XY sex chromosome pairand receive no athletic benefit, there was a brief dalliance with genetic analysis before the turn toward \\\"suspicion-based testing.\\\"\", \"from\": 2715, \"to\": 2952, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2798, \"end\": 2800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phenotype\", \"score\": 0.7639596580309697, \"rank\": 0.3089696419010971, \"text\": \"XY\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phenotype\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phenotype\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 1980s\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2733}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\": 2769}, {\"ngram\": \"no athletic benefit\", \"from\": 2832, \"to\": 2851}, {\"ngram\": \"a brief dalliance\", \"from\": 2863, \"to\": 2880}, {\"ngram\": \"genetic analysis\", \"from\": 2886, \"to\": 2902}, {\"ngram\": \"the turn\", \"from\": 2910, \"to\": 2918}, {\"ngram\": \"suspicion-based testing\", \"from\": 2927, \"to\": 2950}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Under this system, if someone challenged an athlete's sex, the suspected athlete could be asked to submit to a multifaceted gender verification process.\", \"from\": 2953, \"to\": 3105, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this system\", \"from\": 2959, \"to\": 2970}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 2975, \"to\": 2982}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete's sex\", \"from\": 2994, \"to\": 3010}, {\"ngram\": \"the suspected athlete\", \"from\": 3012, \"to\": 3033}, {\"ngram\": \"a multifaceted gender verification process\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3104}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beginning around 2010,the conversation in international sports turned to natural testosterone levels, the ways that women's bodies responded to that testosterone and specific diagnoses of intersex variations.\", \"from\": 3107, \"to\": 3315, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"2010,the conversation\", \"from\": 3124, \"to\": 3145}, {\"ngram\": \"international sports\", \"from\": 3149, \"to\": 3169}, {\"ngram\": \"natural testosterone levels\", \"from\": 3180, \"to\": 3207}, {\"ngram\": \"women's bodies\", \"from\": 3223, \"to\": 3237}, {\"ngram\": \"that testosterone\", \"from\": 3251, \"to\": 3268}, {\"ngram\": \"specific diagnoses\", \"from\": 3273, \"to\": 3291}, {\"ngram\": \"intersex variations\", \"from\": 3295, \"to\": 3314}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet every version of sex testing collapses under scrutiny.\", \"from\": 3317, \"to\": 3375, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every version\", \"from\": 3321, \"to\": 3334}, {\"ngram\": \"sex testing\", \"from\": 3338, \"to\": 3349}, {\"ngram\": \"scrutiny\", \"from\": 3366, \"to\": 3374}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's because most sports are organized according to a strict male-female binary.Nature is not.\", \"from\": 3376, \"to\": 3472, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"most sports\", \"from\": 3391, \"to\": 3402}, {\"ngram\": \"a strict male-female binary\", \"from\": 3430, \"to\": 3457}, {\"ngram\": \"Nature\", \"from\": 3458, \"to\": 3464}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each Olympic sport is governed by its own international federation, and the International Olympic Committee permits each federation to establish its own eligibility criteria when it comes to issues such as age, citizenship and sex.\", \"from\": 3474, \"to\": 3705, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3550, \"end\": 3581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each Olympic sport\", \"from\": 3474, \"to\": 3492}, {\"ngram\": \"its own international federation\", \"from\": 3508, \"to\": 3540}, {\"ngram\": \"each federation\", \"from\": 3590, \"to\": 3605}, {\"ngram\": \"its own eligibility criteria\", \"from\": 3619, \"to\": 3647}, {\"ngram\": \"issues\", \"from\": 3665, \"to\": 3671}, {\"ngram\": \"age\", \"from\": 3680, \"to\": 3683}, {\"ngram\": \"citizenship\", \"from\": 3685, \"to\": 3696}, {\"ngram\": \"sex\", \"from\": 3701, \"to\": 3704}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2021 \\\"IOC Framework on Fairness, Inclusion and Non-Discrimination on the Basis of Gender Identity and Sex Variations\\\" offers a series of recommendations for federations to consider, but also recognizes that 